d.\nThis is similar to `Polynomial.natDegree` but not to `Polynomial.degree`, namely, the separable\ndegree of `0` is `0`, not negative infinity. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableDegree.html#Polynomial.natSepDegree","kind":"def","line":295,"name":"Polynomial.natSepDegree","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/087469e24922b85cb737497c74556c7dacc01f22/Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableDegree.lean#L295-L299"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/FieldTheory/SeparableDegree.html#Field.finSepDegree_mul_finSepDegree_of_isAlgebraic\"><span class=\"name\">Field</span>.<span class=\"name\">finSepDegree_mul_finSepDegree_of_isAlgebraic</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">F</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> v)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Field/Defs.html#Field\">Field</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Algebra/Defs.html#Algebra\">Algebra</a> <span class=\"fn\">F</span> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> w)</span></span>\n<span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"